            <title>[KAFKA-18100] `Using` block suppresses all errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18100</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/15881&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/15881&lt;/a&gt; changed our tests to utilize `using` blocks. But these blocks don&apos;t throw any errors, so if there is a failed assertion within the block, the test will still pass.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should either check the failure using a corresponding `match` block with Success(_) and Failure(e), use `using.resource`, or use try/finally blocks to clean up resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scala-lang.org/api/3.0.2/scala/util/Using$.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.scala-lang.org/api/3.0.2/scala/util/Using$.html&lt;/a&gt;&#160;**&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
